The paper discusses deep convolutional neural networks and their applications in recognition tasks, which are primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for zero-shot recognition, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of these techniques involves the use of large datasets, which is a common theme in machine learning research (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for zero-shot recognition, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of multimedia data for recognition tasks, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
